    <thetext>Some EPUB reading systems are not proper XML parsers and are unable to parse the OCF file produced by these EPUB tools. As we do not have to use the &quot;ocf&quot; prefaces we should remove it in order to make produced publications compatible. For instance:

&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
&lt;ocf:container xmlns:ocf=&quot;urn:oasis:names:tc:opendocument:xmlns:container&quot; version=&quot;1.0&quot;&gt;
  &lt;ocf:rootfiles&gt;
    &lt;ocf:rootfile full-path=&quot;OEBPS/content.opf&quot; media-type=&quot;application/oebps-package+xml&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;/ocf:rootfiles&gt;
&lt;/ocf:container&gt;

Should be:

&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot;?&gt;
&lt;container version=&quot;1.0&quot; xmlns=&quot;urn:oasis:names:tc:opendocument:xmlns:container&quot;&gt;
  &lt;rootfiles&gt;
    &lt;rootfile full-path=&quot;OEBPS/content.opf&quot; media-type=&quot;application/oebps-package+xml&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;/rootfiles&gt;
&lt;/container&gt;</thetext>
